4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing federal law, the AMBER Alert
6 System sends an alert to assist in the recovery of a
7 child under 17 years of age who a law enforcement
8 agency believes has been abducted and is in imminent
9 danger of serious bodily injury or death.
10 Under existing state law, the Missing and
11 Endangered Persons Alert Act sends an alert when the
12 Alabama State Law Enforcement Agency believes an
13 individual has been abducted and has a reasonable
14 belief that the individual is at risk of bodily harm or
15 death.
16 This bill would create an Ebony Alert System to
17 send an alert to assist in the recovery of a Black
18 youth or young adult, under certain circumstances.
