29 Section 1. (a) For purposes of this section, "Ebony
30 Alert" means a notification system, activated pursuant to
31 subsection (b), designed to issue and coordinate alerts for
32 Black youth, including young women and girls, who are reported
33 missing under unexplained or suspicious circumstances.
34 (b)(1) If an individual is reported missing to a law
35 enforcement agency and that agency, referencing the factors in
36 subsection (c), determines that an alert would assist in the
37 search and rescue of the individual, the law enforcement
38 agency may request the Alabama State Law Enforcement Agency
39 (ALEA) to activate an Ebony Alert.
40 (2) If ALEA concurs with the assessment of the factors
41 in subsection (c), ALEA shall activate an Ebony Alert within
42 the appropriate geographical area requested by the
43 investigating law enforcement agency.
44 (3) Radio, television, cable, satellite, and social
45 media systems are encouraged to cooperate with disseminating
46 the information contained in an Ebony Alert.
47 (4) Upon activation of an Ebony Alert, ALEA shall
48 assist the investigating law enforcement agency by issuing a
49 be-on-the-lookout alert, an electronic flyer, or a changeable
50 message sign in compliance with subdivision (5).
51 (5) Upon activation of an Ebony Alert, ALEA may use a
52 changeable message sign if both of the following conditions
53 are met:
54 a. A law enforcement agency determines that a vehicle
55 may be involved in the incident.
56 b. Specific identifying information about the vehicle
