57 is available for public dissemination.
58 (c) A law enforcement agency may request that an Ebony
59 Alert be activated if that agency determines that an Ebony
60 Alert would be an effective tool in the investigation of
61 missing Black youth, including a young woman or girl, after
62 considering the following factors:
63 (1) Whether the missing individual is between 12 and 25
64 years of age.
65 (2) Whether the missing individual suffers from a
66 mental or physical disability.
67 (3) Whether the individual is missing under
68 circumstances that indicate any of the following:
69 a. The missing individual's physical safety may be
70 endangered.
71 b. The disappearance of the missing individual may not
72 have been voluntary, including an abduction or kidnapping.
73 c. The missing individual may be subject to
74 trafficking.
75 (4) Whether the law enforcement agency determines that
76 the individual has gone missing under unexplained or
77 suspicious circumstances as determined by the investigation of
78 the law enforcement agency.
79 (5) Whether the law enforcement agency believes any of
80 the following:
81 a. The individual is in danger because of age, health,
82 mental or physical disability, or environmental or weather
83 related conditions.
84 b. The individual is in the company of a potentially
